I'm not a thrifty kind of person so I don't usually have savings.
But where and how can I cough up $150?

My sister lost her tuition fees today and whoa. My mum blew up and started whacking her with the cane. Whacking, not hitting. Then Mum told my sister that she had to find a way to find that $150 herself to pay for the tuition and started pushing(dragging too.) her out the door. Mum told my sister to go down and search for the money and locked her outside. WTF? She's only Primary 5 for goodness sake. Uh and so I called my mum crazy and I opened the door and let her in.
My mum whacked her so hard that my sis was screaming like hell and even my brother tried to search her bag in hope of finding the money. After that, my mum asked about their results. My sis got 60++ to 70++ and my mum whacked her again -.-
My brother failed Chinese and my mum started to whacked him.

My parents don't cane me anymore cus they know it doesn't work for me. I'll just let them hit and call them crazy.
And yeh. Tear a little bit :X
Ok fine. I cry lah can.

So how? What to do?

I still think friends don't make up everything of my life.
It's just part of my life.
And I never mentioned that I don't need friends.
I just implied that I don't need friends from school.

Friends are not everything.

In the garbage bin?

(Do not attempt to read if you are easily offended.)
(If you think it's you I'm talking about, try leaving a comment.)

All comments are screened :)

Why am I even friends with you in the first place?
I've known you for so long. So so long.
And I can't believe it. I'm still in doubt. 
I mean, fuck. I hate your attitude.
Sometimes you're like taking people for granted.
Other times you're treating people as your best friends.
And most of the times you're acting as if you're all-that. You rule the entire world.
Bloody hell. I hate that.

I don't like frienemies.
It's either you're my much loved friend, or you're an outsider.
I don't care whether people hate me or not. 
I just like doing what I like to do. Even if it bothers you, that's your business. 
Don't come bothering me about how much you hate me. Cus that's stupid. 

Mind your own fucking business.

You know, sometimes friends aren't everything that makes up your life.
And I've learnt something.
Never ever put your friends before you. It's rather stupid. (If you think otherwise then that's your problem.)
I am never ever going to talk to anyone in class except for those nice people like Jun Teck, Amirah, Sarina, Yoke Teng and all.
If you're unhappy then so be it. Avoid me for all I care.
Don't even talk to me. Badmouth me. Curse me. Whatever.
It's only 3 months till everything is over.
Just 3 more flippin' months and I can do whatever I want. I don't need to hang out with secondary school mates. 
I've got friends out there for heaven's sake!
Bloody hell.

Now I feel so much better after ranting.
K goodbye. I hope nothing serious happens during the picnic tomorrow.
I'd feel damn fucked.

That is so not me. Hahaha.

But sad enough, it IS me. Another face of mine in fact, I guess.
As much as you've changed over the decade, I've changed  just as much as I possibly did. Wierd innit? I felt as if 2 seconds ago I was just beginning to enter nursery(I couldn't stop crying) and I called my teacher Ah-Ma -.-
Just 3 seconds ago I just entered Keming Pri and getting bullied by all the freaking boys! Hair pulling.. Racing against each other in the field during recess. Mind you, I still remember the people I've mixed with in primary school ok. Also, in Unity. I socialised with more girls this time though. Was more engaged in CCA rather then in Keming though. Track & field, netball, house activities. Nearly was house captain but I pushed it away so Nizza got it instead.

And then there was this period of time where I went to China for 6 months before I couldn't take it and flew back ASAP. I'm not being racist or anything. I wasn't really able to adapt to their environment there. But I'll never ever forget the 2 best friends I had. They were both boys, one was a Korean and another was from HongKong. My total best friends. We hung out everywhere. I played gameboy and exchanged games with the Hongkong guy. I went over to the Korean's for dinner. It was totally fab. 

But I disappeared suddenly, so I don't think they'll ever remember me. Or my name, for a matter of fact. It's rather a pity. Sometimes these memories just churn out from nowhere at all. Damn. The condo I lived in was full of foreign people like me. Asians, Caucasians. Bloody hell there were alot of ang mohs ok. But none of the closer ones were of my age. Seriously, I miss playing with them :(

Do you have any childhood friends whom you've lost contact with?
Btw, new class blog at http://qetesh.pseudocide.net/ :D

Are guys really that clueless and insensitive?
Sometimes it's goddamn annoying to see boy groupies walking pass you and passing really insulting remarks among themselves. And worse. You happened to hear those insensitive comments. And yet some, I was playing dota and really. Some guys were ruining it for me. They actually blurted Harry Potter's ending out to me. What the fuck? Luckily, they were just trying to bloody show off. (As always.) I checked it online. They were wrong about the goddamn ending. Whew.

200 pounds beauty was right.
Most men feel that plastic surgery is alright for women but they don't like their women to have plastic surgery.
What's wrong with having small boobies? (Luckily my boyf doesn't care about my figure, lol. He thinks I'm not skinny! Hahaha.)

Pffs. 
They are bloody fucking annoying you know? Trust me. I've have had this kind of experience where they pass remarks aloud right next to you. And please lah, it's damn obvious. I realised though, 99.999999999% of the boys are fucking felonrys. God they are so bloody ugly. Fashion sense? NADA. Most of them have this long long long fringe where they put to the side. Oh for fuck's sake it's hell ugly.

Fuck you insensitive dirty scums of the earth.
